{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"doughy-sulfuryl-spiketail","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Defect\n\n`rebar review-plan` crashes on the attestation-persistence path with:\n\n```\nTypeError: _with_index_lock_retry() got an unexpected keyword argument 'force_reclaim'\n```\n\n(observed exit code 11) when two or more `review-plan` runs race the ticket-index lock\nconcurrently — e.g. several plan reviews launched in parallel. The signing/persist step calls\n`_with_index_lock_retry(..., force_reclaim=...)` but the retry helper does not accept that\nkeyword, so the attestation write aborts.\n\n## Impact\n\n- The review body completes and `signature.signed` may be reported `true` on stdout, but the\n  attestation is **not persisted** to the store — `rebar audit show <id>` shows no signature.\n  So stdout `signed=true` is not a reliable indicator of a durable signature under contention.\n- Forces plan-review gating to be run strictly serially to avoid the crash; parallel review of\n  an epic + its children (the natural batch operation) is unsafe.\n\n## Repro (observed)\n\n1. Launch >=2 `rebar review-plan <id>` runs concurrently against tickets sharing the index lock.\n2. One or more crash with the `force_reclaim` TypeError (EXIT=11) on the persist step.\n\n## Suggested fix direction\n\nReconcile the caller/callee signatures on the index-lock retry path\n(`_with_index_lock_retry` and the attestation-persist caller in the workflow/orchestrator\nlayer): either add/accept the `force_reclaim` parameter on `_with_index_lock_retry` or stop\npassing it. Add a regression test that persists an attestation while the index lock is\ncontended.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Concurrent `review-plan` runs contending the index lock persist their attestations\n  without raising `TypeError: ... force_reclaim`.\n- [ ] `rebar audit show <id>` reflects the persisted signature after a contended review.\n- [ ] A regression test exercises the contended-persist path.","id":"d2c4-4084-f88a-4d98","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"review-plan attestation-persist crashes: _with_index_lock_retry() unexpected kwarg force_reclaim under lock contention"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784746467741019001,"uuid":"4950994b-d864-48d9-9c14-a905f427d7b3"}